    public class BankingSystemClient
extends javax.swing.JFrame

    This class represents the GUI and logic of the client of the banking system.

    The class is JFrame which has PanelContainer with a card layout which contains 4 panels bankChoicePanel, loginPanel, mainMenuPanel and transactionHistoryPanel.

    First the user chooses which bank to connect to in bankChoicePanel. If connection is successful, the user is redirected to loginPanel where he/she can login using username and password. If login is successful the user is redirected to mainMenuPanel where he/she deposit,withdraw or transfer money or logout. The user can also view the transaction history which redirects to transactionHistoryPanel. The user can get back to mainMenuPanel by pressing a back button.

      • historyButtonActionPerformed

        private void historyButtonActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)

        This function is called when Transaction History button in the mainMenuPanel is pressed.

        It sends the server requests in the form HST:offset and the server response will be 5 transaction starting from offset.

        TODO: refrence documentation of server

        Transaction Formats:-

        • Deposit ==> timestamp,DEP,amount,balanceAfterTransaction
        • Withdraw ==> timestamp,WTD,amount,balanceAfterTransaction
        • Incoming Transfer ==> timestamp,TRFIN,bank,accNo,amount,balance
        • Outgoing Transfer ==> timestamp,TRFOUT,bank,accNo,amount,balance

        Each of the 5 transactions sent by the server is separated by # from the other transactions. If there are less than 5 transactions remaining, the server will send keyword end after the last transaction.

        example:-
        Say that the user has 7 transactions in transaction history. and client sent request HST:0 the server will send the first 5 transactions like this
        HST:1480564488236,DEP,100000,100000#1480714421456,WTD,20000,80000#1480814598752,TRFOUT,bank 2,28754,5000,75000#1480914599999,TRFIN,bank 1,21458,6000,81000#1480104651548,DEP,2540,100,81100

        when client next sends HST:5 the server response will be the next 5 transaction starting from transaction number 6 but because there's only 7 transactions the server will send transactions 6 and 7 then the keyword end
        HST:1481104651548,DEP,500,81600#1481204651548,WTD,2000,79600#end

        Parameters:
        evt -

      • transferButtonActionPerformed

        private void transferButtonActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
        This function is called when transfer button in the manMenu is pressed (The user wants to transfer money to another account). It sends the server a transfer request in the form TRF:bank,accNo,ammount The server response will either be
        • TRF:0 ==> means transfer successful.
        • TRF:1 ==> means transfer failed.
        • TRF:2 ==> means balance is not enough.
        • TRF:3 ==> means server couldn't connect to the other bank.
        • TRF:4 ==> means server couldn't find that account.
        Parameters:
        evt -

      • getAccountInfo

        private java.lang.String getAccountInfo()
        Returns a string representing the account information of the user. It sends a request to the server in the form INF: requesting the user information. The server response is in the form INF:accountNo,firstName,LastName,userName,email,balance
        Returns:
        A string representing the user account information. This string is in the form accountNo,firstname,lastname,username,email,balance.

        ex:- INF:25487,abdullah,abdelrazik,limbo,abdallah.abdoooo@hotmail.com,5480
